1
00:00:48,014 --> 00:00:49,047
Dong Hwa!

2
00:00:50,510 --> 00:00:53,088
Dong Hwa, wake up!

3
00:00:55,616 --> 00:00:59,488
What? How did you get down here?

4
00:00:59,488 --> 00:01:00,736
What's all this?

5
00:01:01,454 --> 00:01:02,654
Why are you here?

6
00:01:03,554 --> 00:01:04,800
Where's the killer?

7
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:05,920
Killer?

8
00:01:06,638 --> 00:01:07,805
What do you mean?

9
00:01:08,472 --> 00:01:09,805
Don't you know?

10
00:01:09,805 --> 00:01:12,938
That guy in my house upstairs.
He's here to kill me.

11
00:01:14,338 --> 00:01:15,372
What?

12
00:01:16,072 --> 00:01:18,538
He locked you up like this?

13
00:01:19,505 --> 00:01:20,538
Why?

14
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:22,372
I don't know.

15
00:01:23,072 --> 00:01:25,505
He showed up out of nowhere to kill me,

16
00:01:25,505 --> 00:01:28,072
but he didn't. He just locked me up here.

17
00:01:28,072 --> 00:01:30,105
See that lock over there?

18
00:01:30,105 --> 00:01:32,905
That punk up there probably has the key.

19
00:01:32,905 --> 00:01:34,738
He always takes it out of his pants.

20
00:01:34,738 --> 00:01:37,905
Dong Hwa, then I'll call Chul Jin.

21
00:01:37,905 --> 00:01:39,372
- Chul Jin...
- No, you can't.

22
00:01:39,372 --> 00:01:42,805
You can't trust the police in Dongcheon.

23
00:01:44,072 --> 00:01:46,672
Tae Jeong, please, I'm begging you.

24
00:01:47,405 --> 00:01:49,805
You're the only one I can trust.

25
00:01:51,105 --> 00:01:52,405
Okay, I'll look into it.

26
00:01:58,072 --> 00:01:59,072
Chu Tae Jeong?

27
00:02:38,205 --> 00:02:39,605
First, find the phone.

28
00:02:40,238 --> 00:02:42,138
We'll talk after that.

29
00:03:24,805 --> 00:03:26,005
What are you doing?

30
00:03:28,805 --> 00:03:32,072
That guy in my house upstairs.
He's here to kill me.

31
00:03:36,172 --> 00:03:38,072
I didn't check this side.

32
00:03:39,772 --> 00:03:41,238
Where have you been?

33
00:03:46,772 --> 00:03:50,038
I've been home the whole time.
In the inner office.

34
00:03:51,738 --> 00:03:52,738
Really?

35
00:03:55,038 --> 00:03:56,238
Did you find anything?

36
00:03:58,638 --> 00:04:01,372
That punk up there probably has the key.

37
00:04:01,372 --> 00:04:03,372
He always takes it out of his pants.

38
00:04:07,272 --> 00:04:08,872
What are you looking at?

39
00:04:14,938 --> 00:04:15,938
Huh?

40
00:04:17,838 --> 00:04:18,872
Nothing.

41
00:04:25,905 --> 00:04:27,572
What's this on your hair?

42
00:04:28,538 --> 00:04:29,572
You're so clumsy.

43
00:04:30,272 --> 00:04:31,605
What have you been up to?

44
00:04:35,057 --> 00:04:36,785
What's going on with you?

45
00:04:40,305 --> 00:04:42,105
No, it's nothing.

46
00:05:02,605 --> 00:05:05,338
That punk up there probably has the key.

47
00:05:05,338 --> 00:05:07,338
He always takes it out of his pants.

48
00:05:59,738 --> 00:06:00,805
What are you doing?

49
00:06:04,838 --> 00:06:06,372
I said, what are you doing?

50
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:13,472
I don't know either.

51
00:06:14,505 --> 00:06:15,505
What?

52
00:06:20,905 --> 00:06:22,938
You should tuck in when you're sleeping.

53
00:06:26,938 --> 00:06:27,972
Jeez.

54
00:06:53,838 --> 00:06:55,405
This is driving me nuts.

55
00:07:06,772 --> 00:07:08,905
Why do you think Min Ho died?

56
00:07:08,905 --> 00:07:10,972
Because he failed to eliminate the target.

57
00:07:12,505 --> 00:07:17,405
"Why couldn't he kill the target?"
I thought about it.

58
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:20,672
I think it was because he was a good person.

59
00:07:22,538 --> 00:07:26,638
That's why he wanted to start fresh
with the woman he was supposed to kill.

60
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:28,838
How stupid.

61
00:07:46,138 --> 00:07:47,638
You're up.

62
00:07:53,338 --> 00:07:54,372
Drink up.

63
00:07:56,005 --> 00:07:57,305
Thank you.

64
00:08:07,472 --> 00:08:09,105
You look tired.

65
00:08:11,972 --> 00:08:13,905
Why did you come out last night?

66
00:08:15,672 --> 00:08:18,372
What, do you need something from me?

67
00:08:19,205 --> 00:08:24,138
To see the scar on your chest.
It looked huge.

68
00:08:27,438 --> 00:08:28,938
I got hurt, a long time ago.

69
00:08:28,938 --> 00:08:32,538
It looked like a knife wound.
How did it happen?

70
00:08:32,538 --> 00:08:34,838
It's nothing. Don't worry about it.

71
00:08:35,705 --> 00:08:38,272
But when your friend
came over the other day...

72
00:08:39,072 --> 00:08:40,772
You mean Chul Jin?

73
00:08:42,228 --> 00:08:44,175
He looked down on you for being a wimp.

74
00:08:44,175 --> 00:08:47,538
It's not like that.
He's just teasing me because we're close.

75
00:08:49,372 --> 00:08:50,572
Yeah, sure.

76
00:08:51,672 --> 00:08:53,872
You couldn't escape and got dragged around.

77
00:09:02,738 --> 00:09:04,172
Hang on.

78
00:09:05,038 --> 00:09:08,305
You must be good at defending yourself
in those situations, right?

79
00:09:12,672 --> 00:09:14,638
Alright, come at me.

80
00:09:16,872 --> 00:09:18,572
I'll really do it.

81
00:09:25,372 --> 00:09:26,438
Take it easy.

82
00:09:26,438 --> 00:09:28,938
Are you really a cop?

83
00:09:28,938 --> 00:09:30,805
You just came at me so suddenly.

84
00:09:35,005 --> 00:09:37,872
What criminal gives you time to get prepared?

85
00:09:37,872 --> 00:09:40,405
See, this is why your friend
bosses you around.

86
00:09:40,405 --> 00:09:41,638
I told you it wasn't like that.

87
00:09:41,638 --> 00:09:44,872
Whatever. When someone
rushes at you like this,

88
00:09:45,505 --> 00:09:50,372
just hit down their left arm like I just did,
or quickly step inside. Got it?

89
00:09:51,805 --> 00:09:52,838
Okay.

90
00:09:54,005 --> 00:09:57,838
Hey, can you teach me
how to escape a headlock?

91
00:10:00,172 --> 00:10:02,672
Okay, put me in a headlock.

92
00:10:06,305 --> 00:10:08,705
So, there are a few ways to do it.
It's simple.

93
00:10:08,705 --> 00:10:11,838
You can turn around
and flip them over like I just did.

94
00:10:11,838 --> 00:10:14,805
Or grab the closest leg
and take them down backwards.

95
00:10:17,705 --> 00:10:19,572
How's that? Easy, right?

96
00:10:20,872 --> 00:10:22,472
How is this easy?

97
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:25,684
What's so hard about it?

98
00:10:25,684 --> 00:10:27,471
You're much bigger than me.

99
00:10:27,471 --> 00:10:30,138
You can't pick and choose
smaller guys on the job.

100
00:10:33,005 --> 00:10:35,972
Let me teach you an easy one. Grab me.

101
00:10:38,272 --> 00:10:40,038
Lower your body a bit more.

102
00:10:40,038 --> 00:10:42,838
- Go easy on me.
- Try to stretch out your right arm.

103
00:10:42,838 --> 00:10:45,872
Lower your body, extend your right arm,
add some strength...

104
00:10:51,605 --> 00:10:54,472
What are you doing?

105
00:10:54,472 --> 00:10:55,472
Sorry.

106
00:10:58,805 --> 00:11:00,072
Alright, last one.

107
00:11:00,917 --> 00:11:02,072
Try to throw me.

108
00:11:05,663 --> 00:11:08,344
Lower your body a bit more
and push your hips back.

109
00:11:08,344 --> 00:11:09,538
Now try again.

110
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:14,983
Gosh, you're hopeless.

111
00:11:14,983 --> 00:11:16,938
You really need to lift some weights.

112
00:11:17,705 --> 00:11:19,305
Oh, forget it. I give up.

113
00:11:20,138 --> 00:11:21,805
I'm done.

114
00:11:54,805 --> 00:11:56,938
I'll go wash up first.

115
00:12:14,438 --> 00:12:16,672
Lower your body a bit more.

116
00:12:16,672 --> 00:12:18,905
Try to stretch out your right arm.

117
00:12:26,138 --> 00:12:28,657
How did you get down here?
Where is that punk?

118
00:12:28,657 --> 00:12:31,858
He's taking a shower. I have to hurry.

119
00:12:31,858 --> 00:12:33,437
You found it.

120
00:12:33,437 --> 00:12:34,905
I went through his pockets.

121
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:37,005
What?

122
00:12:38,972 --> 00:12:40,338
How is that possible?

123
00:12:48,705 --> 00:12:50,005
You've done well.

124
00:12:50,905 --> 00:12:52,238
What?

125
00:12:52,238 --> 00:12:55,072
We picked up Heo Dong Hwa's phone signal.

126
00:12:55,072 --> 00:12:57,238
Ah, right.

127
00:12:57,238 --> 00:13:00,172
Now leave that house. Your job is done.

128
00:13:01,005 --> 00:13:03,438
What do you mean, done?

129
00:13:03,438 --> 00:13:05,638
I haven't taken care of Heo Dong Hwa yet.

130
00:13:05,638 --> 00:13:07,838
You don't need to worry about that anymore.

131
00:13:08,538 --> 00:13:10,138
I had Hyeon handle the rest.

132
00:13:13,772 --> 00:13:17,372
Since it seems you have no intention
of finishing him off.

133
00:13:17,372 --> 00:13:18,838
I'll do it.

134
00:13:20,238 --> 00:13:22,638
How much further
are you going to let me down?

135
00:13:26,372 --> 00:13:28,572
The time the phone was turned on.

136
00:13:30,505 --> 00:13:32,038
It was last night.

137
00:13:34,038 --> 00:13:35,505
What's wrong?

138
00:13:35,505 --> 00:13:37,238
This isn't the right key.

139
00:13:37,938 --> 00:13:39,305
Is there another one?

140
00:13:40,372 --> 00:13:44,085
Sorry. I'll go find it.

141
00:13:44,085 --> 00:13:45,138
Be careful.

142
00:13:50,805 --> 00:13:52,505
Why didn't you report it sooner?

143
00:13:54,398 --> 00:13:57,605
You're still not telling me
about Chu Tae Jeong.

144
00:14:00,105 --> 00:14:02,805
Did you think I wouldn't know about you two?

145
00:14:05,991 --> 00:14:09,172
You're not thinking
of starting over too, are you?

146
00:14:10,938 --> 00:14:12,705
I'll give you one last chance.

147
00:14:15,358 --> 00:14:18,005
Would you prefer Chu Tae Jeong
to get killed by you?

148
00:14:19,538 --> 00:14:21,372
Or by Hyeon?

149
00:14:27,072 --> 00:14:29,605
Hey, what are you doing?

150
00:14:30,638 --> 00:14:32,872
- I found the phone.
- What?

151
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,972
The proof I told you about. I found it.

152
00:14:34,972 --> 00:14:36,472
Pack up. We have to get out.

153
00:14:36,472 --> 00:14:37,938
But I'm staying here.

154
00:14:41,705 --> 00:14:43,238
What?

155
00:14:43,238 --> 00:14:45,772
I'll wait until Dong Hwa comes back.

156
00:14:45,772 --> 00:14:49,345
Chu Tae Jeong, how do you know
if or when he will return?

157
00:14:49,345 --> 00:14:52,372
He'll come back. I trust Dong Hwa.

158
00:14:55,372 --> 00:14:59,527
What on earth makes you trust Heo Dong Hwa?

159
00:14:59,527 --> 00:15:00,772
Heo Dong Hwa is a thug.

160
00:15:00,772 --> 00:15:03,472
He's a piece of trash
with no sense of responsibility.

161
00:15:05,605 --> 00:15:09,738
What are you two?
Are you really just friends?

162
00:15:11,947 --> 00:15:13,705
Why are you so mad all of a sudden?

163
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:18,605
Come on. Pack your things.

164
00:15:19,834 --> 00:15:23,305
Like I said, I'll wait for Dong Hwa here.

165
00:15:23,305 --> 00:15:25,738
Yeah? Then go ahead.

166
00:15:27,305 --> 00:15:28,738
What are you doing?

167
00:15:28,738 --> 00:15:30,272
I won't say it again.

168
00:15:31,761 --> 00:15:32,905
Pack your things.

169
00:15:33,872 --> 00:15:35,338
Leave all you want.

170
00:15:36,238 --> 00:15:37,905
There's no reason for me to go.

171
00:15:38,884 --> 00:15:41,505
Tae Jeong, get out now, or you're dead!

172
00:15:41,505 --> 00:15:44,584
Why? I didn't do anything!

173
00:15:44,584 --> 00:15:46,205
Because I'm going to kill you.

174
00:15:46,838 --> 00:15:51,372
Liar. But you didn't,
even though you could have.

175
00:15:51,372 --> 00:15:53,172
Shut up.

176
00:15:53,172 --> 00:15:56,072
Or are you going to lock me
in the basement like you did with Dong Hwa?

177
00:15:56,772 --> 00:16:00,438
Do it. If you can.

